From b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2b2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 12:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] avfilter: add vmaf_pre filter (learned pre-processing)

New video filter `vmaf_pre` that runs a residual CNN (C3 in Lusoris
libvmaf's tiny-AI matrix) to pre-process luma planes before encoding.
Uses the standalone vmaf_dnn_session_* public API — no scoring path is
exercised. Requires libvmaf built with --enable_dnn.

Options:
  model   - path to .onnx learned-filter model (required)
  device  - auto | cpu | cuda | openvino | rocm (default: auto)
  threads - CPU EP intra-op threads (default: 0)

Rebased against FFmpeg n8.1. The filter uses the FFFilter struct layout
(`.p.name`, `.p.description`, ...) introduced in n8.0.

Signed-off-by: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
